[size=4][b]RipperMod Manager[/b][/size]

[size=3][b]Why This Exists[/b][/size]

Hey chooms. I got tired of the same old drek — 200+ mods installed locally in Cyberpunk 2077, scattered across a dozen folders, and not a single mod manager out there that could detect them properly. Existing tools just don't sync well with Cyberpunk's mod structure. They can't see what's already on your drive, they can't match your files to Nexus, and half the time you're managing everything by hand like some gonk with a spreadsheet.

So I built RipperMod Manager — a ripperdoc for your mod library. It scans your game folder, figures out which files belong together, links them to their Nexus Mods pages, and gives you full control over everything. AI-powered, Nexus-integrated, and built from the ground up for the Cyberpunk 2077 modding community (though it works with any game on Nexus Mods).

No more guessing which mod broke your game. No more manually tracking 200 mods across folders. Time to chrome up, choom.

[size=3][b]Features[/b][/size]

[b]Mod Scanner & Grouping[/b]
[list]
[*]Automatically scans your game folder and discovers all installed mod files — no matter how many you've got.
[*]Groups scattered files that belong to the same mod using TF-IDF clustering — even when they are spread across multiple directories (mods, archive_mods, red4ext, bin, etc.).
[*]Reads FOMOD and REDmod metadata to improve grouping accuracy.
[*]Streaming progress indicator with phase-by-phase feedback during scans.
[/list]

[b]Auto-Matching (Scan & Correlate)[/b]
This is the preem stuff. RipperMod automatically links your locally installed mods to their Nexus Mods pages using a multi-tier matching pipeline:
[list]
[*][b]Filename ID extraction[/b] — Parses mod IDs embedded in archive filenames.
[*][b]MD5 hash matching[/b] — Matches downloaded archives against Nexus file hashes (gold standard, zero guesswork).
[*][b]Endorsed & Tracked sync[/b] — Cross-references your Nexus endorsed/tracked lists with local files.
[*][b]Fuzzy matching[/b] — Jaccard + Jaro-Winkler similarity scoring as a fallback.
[*][b]AI semantic search[/b] — Optional ChromaDB-powered vector search for the hardest-to-match mods (requires OpenAI API key).
[*]Displays a confidence score on every match so you know how reliable it is.
[*]Deduplication ensures only the best match per Nexus mod is kept.
[/list]

[b]Match Review Actions[/b]
The algorithm does the heavy lifting, but you're the one calling the shots:
[list]
[*][b]Accept / Confirm[/b] — Approve an automatic match with one click.
[*][b]Reject[/b] — Remove an incorrect match so the mod can be re-matched.
[*][b]Correct / Reassign[/b] — Manually search for the right Nexus mod by name, paste a Nexus URL, or enter a mod ID directly.
[/list]

[b]FOMOD Installer[/b]
[list]
[*]Full FOMOD wizard that parses ModuleConfig.xml from archives.
[*]Multi-step conditional UI with plugin groups, dependency resolution, and visual indicators (Required, Recommended, Optional, Not Usable).
[*]Preview file selections before installing.
[*]Supports composite dependencies (AND/OR/XOR conditions).
[/list]

[b]Mod Installation & Management[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Install[/b] from downloaded archives with automatic conflict detection.
[*][b]Uninstall[/b] mods cleanly with confirmation.
[*][b]Enable / Disable[/b] individual mods without removing them.
[*][b]Conflict resolution[/b] dialog showing exactly which files overlap, with Overwrite, Skip, or Cancel options.
[*][b]Bulk operations[/b] — Select multiple mods and enable, disable, or uninstall them all at once.
[*][b]Archive cleanup[/b] — Remove orphan archives not linked to any installed mod.
[/list]

[b]Nexus Mods Integration[/b]
[list]
[*][b]SSO Login[/b] — Sign in with your Nexus Mods account via the official SSO flow. No manual API key needed.
[*][b]Endorsed mods tab[/b] — Browse all mods you have endorsed on Nexus, with quick install buttons.
[*][b]Tracked mods tab[/b] — Browse all mods you are tracking on Nexus.
[*][b]Trending mods tab[/b] — See popular and recently updated mods for your game.
[*][b]Endorse / Abstain[/b] — Toggle endorsement on any mod directly from the app.
[*][b]Track / Untrack[/b] — Toggle tracking on any mod directly from the app.
[*][b]Mod detail view[/b] — Full mod info: banner image, description, author, category, endorsement count, version history, file listings (Main/Update/Optional/Old/Misc), changelogs, and a direct link to the Nexus page.
[/list]

[b]Download Manager[/b]
[list]
[*]Download mods directly from Nexus Mods with real-time progress tracking (bytes and percentage).
[*]Supports premium download speeds for eligible Nexus accounts.
[*][b]NXM protocol handler[/b] — Click "Download with manager" links on the Nexus Mods website and RipperMod handles them automatically.
[*]Queue multiple downloads.
[*]Downloaded archives appear in the Archives tab, ready for installation.
[/list]

[b]Update Checker[/b]
[list]
[*]Detects which of your installed mods have newer versions available on Nexus.
[*]Shows local vs. Nexus version comparison with detection method indicators.
[*]Aggregated Updates page across all games, plus per-game update tables.
[*]One-click download of the latest version.
[/list]

[b]Profile Manager[/b]
Got multiple playthroughs? Different mod loadouts for different builds? Profiles have you covered:
[list]
[*][b]Create[/b] — Snapshot your current mod setup (installed mods + enabled/disabled states) with a name and description.
[*][b]Load[/b] — Restore a saved profile with a diff preview showing what will change before applying.
[*][b]Duplicate[/b] — Copy an existing profile with a new name.
[*][b]Delete[/b] — Remove profiles you no longer need.
[*][b]Export[/b] — Download a profile as a JSON file to share with other chooms.
[*][b]Import[/b] — Upload a JSON profile file.
[*][b]Compare[/b] — Side-by-side comparison of two profiles to see the differences.
[/list]

[b]AI-Powered Features (Optional)[/b]
This is where RipperMod gets its chrome. All AI features are optional — the app works fully without them:
[list]
[*][b]AI Search[/b] — Toggle AI-assisted matching during Scan & Correlate for better results on hard-to-match mods. Uses ChromaDB vector search with OpenAI embeddings.
[*][b]Chat Assistant[/b] — An AI chat panel where you can ask questions about your mod library in plain English (e.g., "which mods are outdated?", "do I have any lighting mods?"). Supports streaming responses, tool calls, and suggested actions.
[*][b]Model selection[/b] — Choose between [b]gpt-5-mini[/b] (cost-optimized, recommended for most chooms) and [b]gpt-5.2[/b] (best quality, for when you need preem results) in Settings.
[*][b]Reasoning effort[/b] — Adjust from none to high to control how much the AI "thinks" before answering. Lower effort = faster and cheaper, higher effort = more accurate.
[*]Requires an OpenAI API key (configured in Settings).
[/list]

[b]Game Management[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Auto-detection[/b] — Automatically finds game installations from Steam, GOG, and Epic registries (including multi-library Steam setups).
[*][b]Manual setup[/b] — Browse and select your game folder manually with path validation.
[*][b]Play button[/b] — Launch your game directly from the app.
[*]Configurable mod directories per game.
[*]Dashboard with overview stats: total games, total mods, Nexus matches, available updates.
[/list]

[b]App Auto-Update[/b]
[list]
[*]Automatically checks for new versions of RipperMod Manager on startup.
[*]Download and install updates directly from Settings with a progress bar.
[*]One-click restart when the update is ready.
[*]Badge on the Settings icon when an update is available.
[/list]

[b]Guided Onboarding[/b]
[list]
[*]Step-by-step setup on first launch — no guesswork:
[list]
[*][b]Step 1[/b] — Welcome screen.
