[size=3][b]How to Install[/b][/size]

[b]1.[/b] Download the latest installer from the [b]Files[/b] tab on this page.
[b]2.[/b] Run the installer and follow the prompts.
[b]3.[/b] Launch RipperMod Manager from your Start Menu or desktop shortcut.

That's it — no additional software required. Everything is bundled in the installer. Future updates are delivered automatically through the app, so you're always running the latest version.

[size=3][b]How to Use[/b][/size]

[b]Step 1: First Launch (Onboarding)[/b]
The app walks you through a quick setup:

[list=1]
[*][b]Nexus Mods Login[/b] — Sign in with your Nexus Mods account via the official SSO flow.
[*][b]Game Setup[/b] — Point the app to your game install folder. For Cyberpunk 2077, it auto-detects Steam, GOG, and Epic installs.
[*][b]Initial Scan[/b] — The app scans your game folder and discovers your installed mods.
[/list]

[b]Step 2: Review Your Mods[/b]
After scanning, your mods are grouped and organized. The app automatically matches them with their Nexus Mods pages so you can see descriptions, versions, and authors. You can [b]Accept[/b], [b]Reject[/b], or [b]Correct[/b] any match.

[b]Tip for better Scan & Correlate results[/b]
For best results, endorse the mods you have installed on Nexus Mods. Tracked mods also help, but the matching pipeline has been tested most extensively with endorsed mods. A quick way to improve matching: review your download history on Nexus and endorse the mods you currently have installed.

[b]Step 3: Manage Your Mods[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Install[/b] — Use the built-in download manager or the Archives tab. FOMOD archives get a full installer wizard.
[*][b]Update[/b] — Check the Updates tab to see which mods have newer versions, then download with one click.
[*][b]Toggle[/b] — Enable or disable any mod without uninstalling it.
[*][b]Profiles[/b] — Save your current setup as a profile and switch between different mod loadouts. Export and share profiles as JSON.
[*][b]Endorse & Track[/b] — Manage your Nexus endorsements and tracking directly from the app.
[/list]

[size=3][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]Windows 10 or 11
[*]A [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/]Nexus Mods[/url] account (free or premium)
[*]An [url=https://platform.openai.com/api-keys]OpenAI API key[/url] (optional — only needed for AI Search and Chat features)
[/list]

[size=3][b]Your Data[/b][/size]

RipperMod Manager stores all mod management data locally on your computer in a SQLite database. The app connects to Nexus Mods to retrieve mod metadata and handle downloads requested by you. If you enable AI features, mod names and descriptions are sent to OpenAI for embedding and chat queries — no personal data is shared.

